    "HFT serves as a significant source of liquidity, so any disruption in their operation results in liquidity being pulled out, especially when AI techniques are widely deployed.",
    "At this point, we have to distinguish two significant impacts of the massive application of AI on the financial markets that result in two sides of the same coin.",
    "First, AI impacts information efficiency by reducing the marginal cost of information acquisition and processing for portfolio managers.",
    "Second, the question is how AI is going to replace human decision, as the machines process much more information faster, making the markets more efficient (Barbopoulos et al., 2021), but at the same time with a higher risk of market manipulation by using spoofing schemes as 2010 Flash Crash (U.S. Department of Justice Office of Public Affairs, 2015) being a source of nonfinancial risk.",
    "In particular, analyzing the interrelation between AI and market conditions and how this relation changes sophisticated investors' behavior has just begun (Chen Y. et al., 2020)."
